In a mixing bowl, beat butter and sugars until crumbly, about 2 minutes. Add the next five ingredients; mix well. Combine dry ingredients; gradually add to the creamed mixture. Stir in chips. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls 2 in. apart onto ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 325 degrees F for 12-14 minutes or until golden brown. Remove to wire racks to cool.